<div type="edition" xml:lang="tam-Latn" rendition="class:tamil maturity:vernacular">

<p>
<lb n="1"/><hi rend="grantha">svasti śrī</hi>
<lb n="2"/>maturai koṇ
<lb n="3"/>ṭa kopparake[<hi rend="grantha">sa</hi>]
<lb n="4"/>ri<hi rend="grantha">panma</hi>ṟku yāṇ
<lb n="5"/>ṭu 10 Āvatu ci
<lb n="6"/>ṟupaḻuvūrt ti
<lb n="7"/>ruvālantuṟai
<lb n="8"/><hi rend="grantha">mahāde</hi>varkku to
<lb n="9"/>ṇṭināṭṭu Erikiḻ
<lb n="10"/>nāṭṭu maṇalūr uṭai
<lb n="11"/>yāṉ mallaṉ kalla
<lb n="12"/>ṟai<hi rend="grantha">candrāditya</hi>vāl Oru
<lb n="13"/>nontāviḷakkeriya
<lb n="14"/>nicatam Uḻakku ney
<lb n="15"/>kku vaitta cāvāmuvāp
<lb n="16"/>perāṭu 90 Itu<hi rend="grantha">panmā</hi>
<lb n="17"/><hi rend="grantha">heśvara rakṣai</hi> ||
</p>

</div>

<div type="apparatus">

</div>

<div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2024_01">

<p>Fortune! Prosperity! This is the 10th year of Kōpparakesarivarman who has taken Madurai. For Mahādeva of Tiruvālantuṟai of Ciṟupaḻuvūr, the lord <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>uṭaiyāṉ</foreign></supplied> of Maṇalūr, of Ērikīḻnāṭu of Toṇṭaināṭu, Mallaṉ Kallaṟai, to burn <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>eriya</foreign></supplied> one perpetual lamp <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>oru nontāviḷakku</foreign></supplied>, as long as the sun and the moon endure, gave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vaitta</foreign></supplied> 90 undying and non-ageing <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>cāvāmūvā</foreign></supplied> great goats <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>perāṭu</foreign></supplied> for one <foreign>uḻakku</foreign> of <foreign>ghee</foreign> <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>neykku</foreign></supplied> every day <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nicatam</foreign></supplied>. This is under the protection of the Panmāheśvaras.</p></div>

